description.narrative: Strengthened capacity at central and municipal levels to develop, budget, and implement a unified, effective system to identify, refer, and address cases of child abuse, exploitation, and neglect for all communities, including Kosovo Serbs, which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Child Protection Systems, Child Protection â€“ Strengthen Families And Communities, Children With Disabilities, Data And Child Protection, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Justice For Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, more boys and girls from the most excluded communities are resilient and benefit from a continuum of child protection services and social protection schemes, responding to violence, neglect, abuse and inequitable access to justice

description.narrative: Through UNICEF support, 3,381 children with disabilities and their parents have benefited from online COVID-19 prevention and protection services including education, psychosocial and family counseling support services. Through the “School opens the world” campaign, a wide range of partners were mobilized on promoting the importance of inclusion of children with disabilities in education. Around 200 children on the move were reached by UNICEF supported programmes and were provided with the necessary materials and essential articles for the prevention of COVID-19. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
